These are scripts to generate a minimal initramfs root filesystem

## Requirements
* multistrap
* network
* root privileges

Steps to install a minimal rootfs:

From this directory execute:
$ sudo multistrap -f multistrap.conf

You should download a linux kernel .deb to this directory, then execute
$ sudo ./install_kernel.sh

# Finally:
$ sudo ./multistrap.post

You'll endup with *.cpio.gz file. This file can be loaded by the kernel. E.g:
$ sudo qemu-system-i386 -m 512 --kernel boot/vmlinuz-3.14-2-486 \
  --initrd initramfs.cpio.gz --serial stdio \
  --append "rdinit=/sbin/init root=/dev/ram0 devtmpfs \
  console=ttyS0 console=tty0 rw"

## Related info:

Since Emdebian is discontinued the multistrap.post script removes files to reduce the footprint

* https://wiki.ubuntu.com/ReducingDiskFootprint

